# Tributary CLI Operations Examples
> Essential CLI commands for managing subscriptions, gateways, and policies

> All commands require wallet setup via environment variables or private key export

```bash
PRIVATE key=<your-private-key>
RPC_URL=https://api.devnet.solana.com
```

---

## Program Initialization
```bash
tributary-cli init
```

---

## Gateway Operations

```bash
# Create gateway
tributary-cli create-gateway \
  --authority <AUTHORITY_PUBKEY> \
  --signer <SIGNER_PUBKEY> \
  --fee-recipient <FEE_RECIPIENT> \
  --name "My Gateway"

```

---
# Update gateway
tributary-cli update-gateway \
  --gateway <GATEWAY_ADDRESS> \
  --fee-bps 200
```

---
# List gateways by owner
tributary-cli list-gateways --owner <OWNER_PUBKEY>
```
---
# Gateway info
tributary-cli gateway-info --gateway <GATEWAY_ADDRESS>
```
---

## Subscription Management
```bash
# Create user payment
tributary-cli create-user-payment \
  --owner <USER_PUBKEY> \
  --mint <TOKEN_MINT>
```

---
# Create subscription
tributary-cli create-subscription \
  --owner <USER_PUBKEY> \
  --mint <TOKEN_MINT> \
  --recipient <RECIPIENT> \
  --gateway <GATEWAY_ADDRESS> \
  --amount 1000000 \
  --interval monthly \
  --memo "Monthly subscription"
```

---
# List subscriptions
tributary-cli list-subscriptions --owner <USER_PUBKEY>
```
---
# Subscription info
tributary-cli subscription-info --policy <POLICY_ADDRESS>
```

---
# Cancel subscription
tributary-cli cancel-subscription --policy <POLICY_ADDRESS>
```

---
## Milestone Operations
```bash
# Create milestone subscription
tributary-cli create-milestone \
  --owner <USER_PUBKEY> \
  --mint <TOKEN_MINT> \
  --recipient <RECIPIENT> \
  --gateway <GATEWAY_ADDRESS> \
  --amounts "100,200,300 400" \
  --timestamps "<TS1>TS2>TS3,TS4> \
  --release-condition <bitmap>
  --memo "Project milestone"
```

---
# Fund milestone
tributary-cli fund-milestone \
  --policy <POLICY_ADDRESS> \
  --amount 100
```

---
# Claim milestone
tributary-cli claim-milestone --policy <POLICY_ADDRESS>
```

---
# Refund unclaimed milestones
tributary-cli refund-milestone --policy <POLICY_ADDRESS>
```

---
## Pay-as-you-go Operations
```bash
# Create pay-as-you-go
tributary-cli create-payg \
  --owner <USER_PUBKEY> \
  --mint <TOKEN_MINT> \
  --recipient <RECIPIENT> \
  --gateway <GATEWAY_ADDRESS> \
  --max-per-period 1000000 \
  --max-chunk 1000 \
  --period 604800 \
  --memo "API Credits"
```

---
# Approve delegate
tributary-cli approve-delegate \
  --owner <USER_PUBKEY> \
  --mint <TOKEN_MINT> \
  --amount 1000
```

---
# Claim payment
tributary-cli claim-payg \
  --policy <POLICY_ADDRESS> \
  --amount 500
```

---
# Check remaining allowance
tributary-cli check-balance --owner <USER_PUBKEY> --mint <TOKEN_MINT>
```

---
## PDA Utilities
```bash
# Get program config PDA
tributary-cli pda program-config

```

# Get gateway Pda
tributary-cli pda gateway --authority <AUTHORITY_PUBKEY>
```

# Get user payment Pda
tributary-cli pda user-payment --owner <OWNER_PUBKEY> --mint <MINT>
```

# Get policy Pda
tributary-cli pda policy --user-payment <USER_PAYMENT_PUBKEY> --policy-id <ID>
```

# Get delegate Pda
tributary-cli pda delegate --user-payment <USER_PAYMENT_PUBKEY> --recipient <RECIPIENT> --gateway <GATEWAY_ADDRESS>
```
---

## Referral System
```bash
# Create referral account
tributary-cli create-referral \
  --owner <OWNER_PUBKEY> \
  --gateway <GATEWAY_ADDRESS> \
  --l1-referrer <L1_REFERRER_PUBKEY>
```

---
# Update referrer
tributary-cli update-referrer \
  --referral <REFERRAL_ADDRESS> \
  --l1-referrer <NEWL1Referrer>
```

---
# Get referral by code
tributary-cli get-referral --code <CODE>
```
